@danmh and @seggenberger can you please provide a ~UX review?

@sdejonge can you provide a ~frontend review?

FYI @igloude

@jeldergl thanks for thinking this through. I'd assumed that pairing would be inevitable - if a thing _is_ a section it would be styled as a section with a section border and section background.

You are right, the descriptions don't indicate that pairing is essential. So I think this would be fine.

I can't help but wonder if we are making these rationalisations based on the desired appearance, rather than the desired semantics :thinking:

**suggestion (non-blocking):** we can use `@apply` rules for these styles as well:

```diff
diff --git a/src/components/base/drawer/drawer.scss b/src/components/base/drawer/drawer.scss
index cde96937e..182077d0d 100644
--- a/src/components/base/drawer/drawer.scss
+++ b/src/components/base/drawer/drawer.scss
@@ -2,12 +2,12 @@ $gl-drawer-width: 400px;
 $gl-sidebar-width: 290px;
 $gl-drawer-scrim-gradient: linear-gradient(
   to bottom,
-  $transparent-rgba,
+  var(--gl-color-alpha-0),
   var(--gl-background-color-overlap)
 );

 .gl-drawer {
-  background-color: var(--gl-background-color-overlap);
+  @apply gl-bg-overlap;
   right: 0;
   @apply gl-transition-all;
   position: fixed;
@@ -49,7 +49,7 @@ $gl-drawer-scrim-gradient: linear-gradient(

   .gl-drawer-body > * {
     @apply gl-mx-5;
-    border-bottom-color: var(--gl-border-color-default);
+    @apply gl-border-b-default;
   }

   .gl-drawer-header {
@@ -58,8 +58,7 @@ $gl-drawer-scrim-gradient: linear-gradient(
 }

 .gl-drawer-footer {
-  @apply gl-border-t-solid gl-border-t-1;
-  border-top-color: var(--gl-border-color-section);
+  @apply gl-border-t-solid gl-border-t-1 gl-border-t-section;
   @apply gl-p-5;
 }

@@ -83,8 +82,7 @@ $gl-drawer-scrim-gradient: linear-gradient(
 }

 .gl-drawer-header {
-  @apply gl-border-b-solid gl-border-b-1;
-  border-bottom-color: var(--gl-border-color-section);
+  @apply gl-border-b-solid gl-border-b-1 gl-border-b-section;
 }

 .gl-drawer-title {
@@ -127,8 +125,7 @@ $gl-drawer-scrim-gradient: linear-gradient(
 }

 .gl-drawer-body > * {
-  @apply gl-border-b-solid gl-border-b-1;
-  border-bottom-color: var(--gl-border-color-section);
+  @apply gl-border-b-solid gl-border-b-1 gl-border-b-section;

   &:last-child {
     @apply gl-border-none;
```

